From c6477cb237048725922f6a786f68b5232abb418f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kevin Lo <kevlo@kevlo.org>
Date: Thu, 21 Oct 2021 14:32:27 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] rtw89: fix return value in hfc_pub_cfg_chk
Git-commit: c6477cb237048725922f6a786f68b5232abb418f
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/kvalo/wireless-drivers-next.git
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository
References: bsc#1191321

It seems to me when pub_cfg->grp0 + pub_cfg->grp1 != pub_cfg->pub_max is true,
it should return -EFAULT rather than 0.  Otherwise, the function doesn't need
to exist.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Lo <kevlo@kevlo.org>
Acked-by: Ping-Ke Shih <pkshih@realtek.com>
Signed-off-by: Kalle Valo <kvalo@codeaurora.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/YXEJey8lKksAZif4@ns.kevlo.org
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw89/mac.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw89/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw89/mac.c
index 69384c43c046..afcd07ab1de7 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw89/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw89/mac.c
@@ -560,7 +560,7 @@ static int hfc_pub_cfg_chk(struct rtw89_dev *rtwdev)
 	const struct rtw89_hfc_pub_cfg *pub_cfg = &param->pub_cfg;
 
 	if (pub_cfg->grp0 + pub_cfg->grp1 != pub_cfg->pub_max)
-		return 0;
+		return -EFAULT;
 
 	return 0;
 }
